.TH cgsix 7D "27 Mar 1992" "SunOS 5.11" "Devices"
.SH NAME
cgsix \- accelerated 8-bit color frame buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
.nf
\fB/dev/fbs/cgsix\fIn\fR
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
\fBcgsix\fR is a low-end graphics accelerator designed to enhance vector
and polygon drawing performance. It has an 8-bit color frame buffer and
provides the standard frame buffer interface as defined in \fBfbio\fR(7I).
.sp
.LP
In addition,
.B cgsix
supports the following \fBcgsix\fR-specific
.BR IOCTL ,
defined in <\fBsys/fbio.h\fR>.
.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B FBIOGXINFO
.ad
.RS 14n
.rt
Returns \fBcgsix\fR-specific information about the hardware.  See the
definition of \fBcg6_info\fR in <\fBsys/fbio.h\fR> for more information.
.RE

.sp
.LP
\fBcgsix\fR has registers and memory that may be mapped with
.BR mmap (2),
using the offsets defined in <\fBsys/cg6reg.h\fR>.
.SH FILES
.sp
.LP
\fB/dev/fbs/cgsix0\fR
.SH SEE ALSO
.sp
.LP
.BR mmap (2),
.BR fbio (7I)
